<TITLE> Child crushed under bundle of rods </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dinajpur, Sept 9 (bdnews24.com)--A child was killed when a bundle of iron rods fell on her at Munshipara upazila in Dinajpur on Tuesday. Three-year old 'Megha' was daughter of Monjurul Haque of Husna of the upazila. Kotwali police chief Hassan Shamim Iqbal said the incident occurred at around 6pm while Megha along with her aunt was passing the road. A bundle of rod fell on her head during offloading from a truck in front of Al Amin Traders, a rod-cement shop. She was rushed to Dinajpur Medical College Hospital in a critical condition and was declared dead by duty doctors, Iqbal said. Local people shut all rod shops of the area in protest against the death. Al Amin Traders owner Abdul Bari and other staffers have remained fugitive since after the incident. 
